main event: Several aerial phenomena were reported over Holloman AFB in New Mexico on April 27 and May 24, 1950.
interesting points: The objects were tracked by radar and reported frequent sightings by professional observers., It was believed that triangulation could be effected but was ultimately not achieved., The observations included objects at approximately 150,000 feet altitude and 30 feet in diameter., The objects were traveling at a high, undetermined speed., No photographs were available for the sightings despite the report from the Data Reduction Unit.
witness description: professional observers and irregular personnel tracking projects
